The 2023 Armed Forces Remembrance Day held at the National Arcade, Eagle Square, Abuja on Sunday. The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, Senate President Ahmad Lawan, Speaker, House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, Chief Justice of Nigeria, Olukayode Ariwoola, service chiefs and other dignitaries attended the wreath-laying ceremony. See photos from the event below:   